This paper deals with the complexity analysis of a scheduling problem, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The problem involves finding an optimal sequence of batches to minimize the weighted number of tardy jobs, which is related to the areas of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), machine learning (cs.LG), and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
